{"type":"message","id":"75f6ab4a","parentId":"a92cb5e5","timestamp":"2026-04-08T11:24:16.838Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Same 405 error. The server doesn't support SSE. Let me check what happens if we try POST without SSE. Maybe there's a different mcporter option for that.\n\nLet me think about this - mcporter might need to use a different transport mode for POST-based MCP servers. Let me check the mcporter docs or help again.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"019d6cd5335c7d82b6bd2ff7ad638ed9","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mcporter --help"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"codingplan","model":"minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":6445,"output":93,"cacheRead":17920,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":24458,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775647451778,"responseId":"019d6cd51fafa7da2126b11599457058"}}
{"type":"message","id":"0cbb9e70","parentId":"75f6ab4a","timestamp":"2026-04-08T11:24:16.201Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"019d6cd5335c7d82b6bd2ff7ad638ed9","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"mcporter — Model Context Protocol CLI & generator\n\nUsage: mcporter <command> [options]\n\nCore commands\n  list  List configured servers (add --schema for tool docs)\n    usage: mcporter list [name] [--schema] [--json]\n  call  Call a tool by selector (server.tool) or HTTP URL; key=value flags supported\n    usage: mcporter call <selector> [key=value ...]\n  auth  Complete OAuth for a server without listing tools\n    usage: mcporter auth <server | url> [--reset]\n\nGenerator & tooling\n  generate-cli  Emit a standalone CLI (supports HTTP, stdio, and inline commands)\n    usage: mcporter generate-cli --server <name> | --command <ref> [options]\n  inspect-cli   Show metadata and regen instructions for a generated CLI\n    usage: mcporter inspect-cli <path> [--json]\n  emit-ts       Generate TypeScript client/types for a server\n    usage: mcporter emit-ts <server> --mode client|types [options]\n\nConfiguration\n  config  Inspect or edit config files (list, get, add, remove, import, login, logout)\n    usage: mcporter config <command> [options]\n\nDaemon\n  daemon  Manage the keep-alive daemon (start | status | stop | restart)\n    usage: mcporter daemon <subcommand>\n\n\nGlobal flags\n  --config <path>                   Path to mcporter.json (defaults to ./config/mcporter.json)\n  --root <path>                     Working directory for stdio servers\n  --log-level <debug|info|warn|error>Adjust CLI logging (defaults to warn)\n  --oauth-timeout <ms>              Time to wait for browser-based OAuth before giving up (default 60000)\n\nQuick start\n  mcporter list\n    # show configured servers\n  mcporter list linear --schema\n    # view Linear tool docs\n  mcporter call linear.list_issues limit:5\n    # invoke a tool with key=value arguments\n  mcporter generate-cli --command https://host/mcp --compile ./my-cli\n    # build a standalone CLI/binary\n\nRun `mcporter <command> --help` for detailed flags.\nmcporter auto-loads servers from ./config/mcporter.json and editor imports (Cursor, Claude, Codex, etc.)."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":-672,"aggregated":"mcporter — Model Context Protocol CLI & generator\n\nUsage: mcporter <command> [options]\n\nCore commands\n  list  List configured servers (add --schema for tool docs)\n    usage: mcporter list [name] [--schema] [--json]\n  call  Call a tool by selector (server.tool) or HTTP URL; key=value flags supported\n    usage: mcporter call <selector> [key=value ...]\n  auth  Complete OAuth for a server without listing tools\n    usage: mcporter auth <server | url> [--reset]\n\nGenerator & tooling\n  generate-cli  Emit a standalone CLI (supports HTTP, stdio, and inline commands)\n    usage: mcporter generate-cli --server <name> | --command <ref> [options]\n  inspect-cli   Show metadata and regen instructions for a generated CLI\n    usage: mcporter inspect-cli <path> [--json]\n  emit-ts       Generate TypeScript client/types for a server\n    usage: mcporter emit-ts <server> --mode client|types [options]\n\nConfiguration\n  config  Inspect or edit config files (list, get, add, remove, import, login, logout)\n    usage: mcporter config <command> [options]\n\nDaemon\n  daemon  Manage the keep-alive daemon (start | status | stop | restart)\n    usage: mcporter daemon <subcommand>\n\n\nGlobal flags\n  --config <path>                   Path to mcporter.json (defaults to ./config/mcporter.json)\n  --root <path>                     Working directory for stdio servers\n  --log-level <debug|info|warn|error>Adjust CLI logging (defaults to warn)\n  --oauth-timeout <ms>              Time to wait for browser-based OAuth before giving up (default 60000)\n\nQuick start\n  mcporter list\n    # show configured servers\n  mcporter list linear --schema\n    # view Linear tool docs\n  mcporter call linear.list_issues limit:5\n    # invoke a tool with key=value arguments\n  mcporter generate-cli --command https://host/mcp --compile ./my-cli\n    # build a standalone CLI/binary\n\nRun `mcporter <command> --help` for detailed flags.\nmcporter auto-loads servers from ./config/mcporter.json and editor imports (Cursor, Claude, Codex, etc.).","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775647456191}}
{"type":"message","id":"2cc2717d","parentId":"0cbb9e70","timestamp":"2026-04-08T11:24:21.820Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"没看到直接支持 POST 而非 SSE 的选项。让我试试直接用 mcporter call 命令，看看是否用不同的方式调用。或者让我看看 mcporter 的 config add 是否支持其他参数。\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"019d6cd60729eaa1adb01f942929b8b9","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mcporter config add --help"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"codingplan","model":"minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":7041,"output":67,"cacheRead":17920,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":25028,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775647456202,"responseId":"019d6cd5f81a25e2dd81c6061e5cc31f"}}
{"type":"message","id":"3e6cf657","parentId":"2cc2717d","timestamp":"2026-04-08T11:24:22.192Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"019d6cd60729eaa1adb01f942929b8b9","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"mcporter config add\nAdds HTTP or stdio servers to the local config. Accepts URLs, commands, env vars, and OAuth metadata.\n\nUsage\n  mcporter config add [options] <name> [target]\n\nFlags\n  --url <https://host>          Set the HTTP/S base URL (implies http transport).\n  --command <binary>            Set the stdio executable (implies stdio transport).\n  --stdio <binary>              Alias for --command.\n  --transport <http|sse|stdio>  Force a specific transport (validates target).\n  --arg <value>                 Pass through additional stdio arguments (repeatable).\n  --description <text>          Set a human-friendly summary.\n  --env KEY=value               Attach environment variables (repeatable).\n  --header KEY=value            Attach HTTP headers (repeatable).\n  --token-cache-dir <path>      Override where OAuth tokens are persisted.\n  --client-name <name>          Customize the OAuth client identifier.\n  --oauth-redirect-url <url>    Set a custom OAuth redirect URL.\n  --auth <strategy>             Force the auth type (e.g., oauth).\n  --copy-from <import:name>     Start with an imported definition by name.\n  --persist <config-path>       Write to an alternate mcporter.json path.\n  --scope <home|project>        Choose whether to write to the home or project config (default: project).\n  --dry-run                     Print the would-be entry without writing to disk.\n  --                            Forward every subsequent token as a stdio arg.\n\nExamples\n  pnpm mcporter config add linear https://mcp.linear.app/mcp\n  pnpm mcporter config add cursor --command \"npx -y cursor\" --arg --stdio"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":337,"aggregated":"mcporter config add\nAdds HTTP or stdio servers to the local config. Accepts URLs, commands, env vars, and OAuth metadata.\n\nUsage\n  mcporter config add [options] <name> [target]\n\nFlags\n  --url <https://host>          Set the HTTP/S base URL (implies http transport).\n  --command <binary>            Set the stdio executable (implies stdio transport).\n  --stdio <binary>              Alias for --command.\n  --transport <http|sse|stdio>  Force a specific transport (validates target).\n  --arg <value>                 Pass through additional stdio arguments (repeatable).\n  --description <text>          Set a human-friendly summary.\n  --env KEY=value               Attach environment variables (repeatable).\n  --header KEY=value            Attach HTTP headers (repeatable).\n  --token-cache-dir <path>      Override where OAuth tokens are persisted.\n  --client-name <name>          Customize the OAuth client identifier.\n  --oauth-redirect-url <url>    Set a custom OAuth redirect URL.\n  --auth <strategy>             Force the auth type (e.g., oauth).\n  --copy-from <import:name>     Start with an imported definition by name.\n  --persist <config-path>       Write to an alternate mcporter.json path.\n  --scope <home|project>        Choose whether to write to the home or project config (default: project).\n  --dry-run                     Print the would-be entry without writing to disk.\n  --                            Forward every subsequent token as a stdio arg.\n\nExamples\n  pnpm mcporter config add linear https://mcp.linear.app/mcp\n  pnpm mcporter config add cursor --command \"npx -y cursor\" --arg --stdio","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775647462180}}
{"type":"message","id":"f0732ecb","parentId":"3e6cf657","timestamp":"2026-04-08T11:24:25.833Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"有一个 `--transport` 选项！可能可以强制使用特定的传输协议。不过 Composio 这个端点只接受 POST，不支持 SSE。让我看看有没有 http transport 可以用纯 HTTP/POST 而不是 SSE。\n\n实际上让我再试试用 curl 直接测试 POST 方法，看看是否能成功调用 tools/list。\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6eaee35a46794ba592007e13","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -X POST \"https://backend.composio.dev/v3/mcp/9dfc9342-cd7f-4c47-b705-c37cdd6b5d77/mcp?user_id=pg-test-Zbs2NXxz5sCER7mGC4PDfrHYJAjBG786\" \\\n  -H \"x-consumer-api-key: ck_8edc9fR2KGT5BrcHiA1Y\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"tools/list\",\"id\":1}' \\\n  --connect-timeout 10 -m 15","timeout":20}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"codingplan","model":"minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":25354,"output":233,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":25587,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775647462193,"responseId":"chatcmpl-242a5cce-e8c8-4df1-9322-5426e40227f7"}}
